      "content": "Proponents often argue that a living wage is a fundamental issue of economic equity and worker dignity, separate from local economic constraints. They point to the risk of prolonged low wages perpetuating cycles of poverty, suggesting that a baseline wage supports broader community health. However, critics counter that mandates without local economic consideration can impose unsustainable burdens, harming established local businesses and employment stability.",
