    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "right, but it feels like a bit of a reach to call it \"equity\" when it actually ends up hurting the very people it's supposed to help by making it harder to keep staff or keep prices low for locals. is there any actual data that shows these hikes don't just cause more job losses in rural areas, or is it mostly just based on that moral argument you mentioned?",
